---
title: "FLAME"
date: "2025-06-23"
category: "poem"
---

Simple vibrations channel breaks in the sky,
Melody of my lightning instrument, I summon thunder.

Dragons stare in wonder and awe as they fly,
Their breath burns in my lungs, and their secrets I plunder.

Fire seeps through my palms and fingers,
Molten earth bubbles in the remains of my footsteps.

The wind knows my name, my distortion lingers,
My blaze spreads, it requires no fuel and lacks precepts.

A rhythmic quaking, bell’s a sounding,
The earth’s a shaking, gong’s a pounding,
The heavens are aching, drums of the heart rounding, surrounding.

The sun sets early away from the horizon,
A chaos so bright, a blinding light, and one prometheus dies in.

Order is dead, structure has fled, have you no shame?
I’ll melt these chains, I’ll grow wings, I know this game.
Chaos, oh chaos, what is your name?
I’ll engulf it all, I’ll leave nothing, I am flame.
